>>17790117
>however, that is more of an explanation not an excuse because I am still working to improve my writing
I haven't worked with creative writing but I have worked with homebrew game design, I've found that trying to explain the cause of your shortcomings causes you to focus on the wrong things and gives the wrong impression.
Rather than thinking "why did I do this badly?" you should totally disregard the reason and instead think "how can I fix this right now?".

Similarly if someone says something is wrong with your writings, don't say "this is why I messed up" but ask "what would make this work for you?".
And again, take that advice and try to iterate on your work with it, rather than leaving it to future you to try and work into future projects.
